Re: Transmittal of SJR 9 Relating to Right of Accused to Confront Children and Other Witnesses
Dear Secretary Pate:
Please find the attached Senate Joint Resolution 9 for filing with your office. The resolution deals with
a proposed amendment to Iowa's Constitution relating to the right of an accused to confront children
and other witnesses. The Iowa General Assembly will initiate the required publication process as
outlined in Iowa's Constitution art. X, sec. 1 and Iowa Code ch. 49A.
Pursuant to Joint Senate/House Rule 21(2), this specific type of" joint resolution" does not require
consideration and signature by the Governor.
